<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>All PDO-Connections to SQL-Server are using the SQL92-Platform-Syntax.</p>

<p>This is done by \Zend\Db\Adapter\Adapter.php in the function createPlatformFromDriver.</p>

<p>So in example a simple query to a MS-SQL-Database looks like this an causes an error:</p>

<p>SELECT "Tablename".* FROM "Tablename"</p>

<p>The "native" Driver "SqlServer" for Microsoft-SQL-Server can only be used on windows platforms. This is not applicable in most cases.</p>

